OL,3,CSkiers and snowboarders enjoy
OL,4,C'England's longest ski slope'
OL,6,FRoy travelled to the ski centre from
OL,7,FSheffield. He told ITV Tyne Tees that
OL,8,Fthe journey was worth it for the
OL,9,F'champagne powder,' and was even
OL,10,Fbetter than the Alps for him.
OL,12,FHe said: "Champagne powder boarders
OL,13,Fcall it, when there are all the little
OL,14,Fglistening crystals because it's so
OL,15,Flight and fluffy. You could just jump
OL,16,Finto a load of powder."
OL,18,F"I've always enjoyed skiing, so having
OL,19,Fsnow here in Weardale absolutely
OL,20,Fgreat," said 81-year-old Alan. "It's a
OL,21,Freally good day."
